1
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:09,075
♪

2
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:18,519
JoJo: WHAT THE HECK
IS THIS SUPPOSED TO BE?

3
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:20,687
YOU THINK YOU'RE FUNNY,

4
00:00:20,787 --> 00:00:22,823
PUTTING BLACK INK
ALL OVER MY SPAGHETTI,

5
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:23,624
IS THAT RIGHT?

6
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,358
Waiter: N‐N‐NO, SIR, NOT AT ALL.

7
00:00:25,425 --> 00:00:27,293
THIS IS CALLED
AL NERO DI SEPPIA.

8
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,962
IT IS A CLASSIC PASTA DISH

9
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:31,331
MADE WITH FRESH SQUID INK,
HENCE THE COLOR.

10
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:32,365
JoJo: REALLY?

11
00:00:32,432 --> 00:00:33,700
Waiter: IT'S QUITE DELICIOUS.

12
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,701
JoJo: HMM.

13
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:37,370
Man: HMM.

14
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:43,644
( gasps )

15
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,379
SAY, THIS IS DELICIOUS!

16
00:00:46,479 --> 00:00:48,014
MMM. ( slurps )

17
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:50,851
MM‐MM‐MM.

18
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:54,721
Man: THIS HOTEL USED TO BE
A PLACE OF CLASS AND REFINEMENT.

19
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:56,890
NOW THEY LET
JUST ANYONE IN HERE.

20
00:00:56,990 --> 00:01:01,535
SIGNORINA, ACCEPT THIS,
A TOKEN OF YOUR BEAUTY.

21
00:01:01,568 --> 00:01:03,069
Woman: IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

22
00:01:03,136 --> 00:01:04,638
Man: NOT AS MUCH AS YOU.

23
00:01:04,705 --> 00:01:07,908
WHEN YOU REMOVE THIS AT NIGHT,
PLEASE THINK OF ME,

24
00:01:07,974 --> 00:01:10,410
AND WE SHALL BE TOGETHER
IN YOUR DREAMS.

25
00:01:10,511 --> 00:01:11,845
JoJo: COME ON!

26
00:01:11,912 --> 00:01:13,413
DID THAT MOZZARELLA CHEESE‐BALL

27
00:01:13,479 --> 00:01:15,181
JUST SAY WHAT I THINK HE SAID?!

28
00:01:15,248 --> 00:01:16,883
I DIDN'T KNOW EAVESDROPPING
COULD ROT YOUR TEETH.

29
00:01:16,917 --> 00:01:18,585
Man: I SHALL CAST
AN ENCHANTMENT UPON IT,

30
00:01:18,652 --> 00:01:20,353
JUST A LITTLE LOVE SPELL,

31
00:01:20,420 --> 00:01:22,422
AND THEN YOU WILL HAVE NO CHOICE

32
00:01:22,488 --> 00:01:24,525
BUT TO FALL TO MY PASSION.
( kiss )

33
00:01:24,591 --> 00:01:26,527
( JoJo shrieks )
YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING.

34
00:01:26,593 --> 00:01:28,328
THIS GUY IS MAKING ME SICK.

35
00:01:28,394 --> 00:01:29,930
( man scoffs )

36
00:01:30,030 --> 00:01:32,432
AND I SHALL SPREAD
MY CHARM'S MAGIC

37
00:01:32,498 --> 00:01:34,768
TO THOSE DELICIOUS LIPS
OF YOURS.

38
00:01:34,835 --> 00:01:36,670
JoJo: THAT'S JUST RIDICULOUS.

39
00:01:36,737 --> 00:01:39,873
HOW COULD ANY MODERN WOMAN FALL
FOR SUCH AN OBVIOUS ACT?

40
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:41,074
DISGUSTING.

41
00:01:41,107 --> 00:01:42,442
I HAVE AN IDEA.

42
00:01:42,509 --> 00:01:45,946
( breathes deeply )

43
00:01:46,046 --> 00:01:47,548
HAMON DI SEPPIA.

44
00:01:47,614 --> 00:01:49,616
THIS SHOULD STICK
TO THAT LITTLE CASANOVA'S

45
00:01:49,716 --> 00:01:52,452
ENCHANTING FACE FOR A BIT.

46
00:01:52,553 --> 00:01:53,854
( chuckles )

47
00:01:55,455 --> 00:01:57,558
( gasps )

48
00:01:59,793 --> 00:02:01,201
( gasps )

49
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:03,436
HOW‐‐HOW DID HE JUST DO THAT?

50
00:02:03,469 --> 00:02:04,638
( slurps )

51
00:02:06,039 --> 00:02:07,741
THAT‐‐THAT WAS HAMON.

52
00:02:07,808 --> 00:02:10,143
YES, I'M SURE OF IT.

53
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:11,645
Waiter: PARDON THE INTRUSION.

54
00:02:11,745 --> 00:02:14,380
BUT THERE IS A PHONE CALL
FROM A MR. SPEEDWAGON,

55
00:02:14,447 --> 00:02:16,116
MR. CAESAR ZEPPELI.

56
00:02:16,149 --> 00:02:18,384
Caesar: MAMMA MIA.
I WILL BE RIGHT THERE.

57
00:02:18,451 --> 00:02:20,386
JoJo: WHAT? WHAT THE‐‐

58
00:02:20,453 --> 00:02:22,889
THAT SPAGHETTI‐BRAINED WOMANIZER

59
00:02:22,956 --> 00:02:26,492
IS THE CAESAR ZEPPELI WE CAME
ALL THE WAY HERE TO FIND?!

60
00:02:26,593 --> 00:02:28,829
( Caesar chuckles )

61
00:02:28,895 --> 00:02:30,831
♪

62
00:02:35,135 --> 00:02:37,070
( singing in Japanese )

63
00:04:01,935 --> 00:04:03,770
♪

64
00:04:04,938 --> 00:04:08,408
Narrator: THIS IS
THE SPEEDWAGON FOUNDATION.

65
00:04:08,441 --> 00:04:10,877
THIS COMPLEX
WAS BUILT 28 YEARS AGO

66
00:04:10,944 --> 00:04:13,914
WITH FUNDS FROM
THE AMPLE SPEEDWAGON FORTUNE.

67
00:04:13,947 --> 00:04:17,951
HERE, ALL MANNERS OF SCIENCE,
MEDICINE, ARCHAEOLOGY, AND MORE

68
00:04:18,018 --> 00:04:20,521
ARE GENEROUSLY FUNDED
AND EXHAUSTIVELY RESEARCHED

69
00:04:20,587 --> 00:04:23,289
FOR THE BENEFIT
OF ALL HUMANKIND.

70
00:04:23,389 --> 00:04:27,127
BUT THE FOUNDATION
ALSO HOUSES A DARKER PURPOSE...

71
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:32,132
ONE TO UNLOCK THE SECRET
OF THE STONE MASKS.

72
00:04:32,232 --> 00:04:34,534
Researcher: THE U. V. LIGHTS
ARE VERY POWERFUL.

73
00:04:34,601 --> 00:04:36,770
PLEASE, IF YOU DON'T MIND.

74
00:04:38,037 --> 00:04:39,773
Researcher #2:
INTRODUCE THE SNAKE.

75
00:04:41,441 --> 00:04:43,977
( snake hissing )

76
00:04:47,614 --> 00:04:48,549
( researchers gasp )

77
00:04:48,615 --> 00:04:49,883
( blood whooshes )

78
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:52,418
Researcher #3:
IT WAS ABSORBED INTO THE STONE!

79
00:04:52,485 --> 00:04:54,588
Researcher #4:
SANTVIENTO STILL ISN'T DEAD.

80
00:04:54,655 --> 00:04:56,590
HIS BODY IS
DEFENDING ITSELF SOMEHOW.

81
00:04:56,657 --> 00:04:58,992
WHAT IF HE FINDS
SOME WAY TO AWAKEN IN THERE?

82
00:04:59,059 --> 00:05:00,160
Researcher #2: THIS CAN'T BE.

83
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:02,235
WE MUST FIND A WAY
TO DESTROY HIM.

84
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:04,170
Researcher #3: THE MONSTER
FEEDS ON MASKED VAMPIRES.

85
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:07,407
HE'S IMMORTAL FOR ALL WE KNOW.
WHAT ARE WE SUPPOSED TO DO?

86
00:05:07,473 --> 00:05:09,342
Researcher #4:
DON'T WORRY, MR. SPEEDWAGON.

87
00:05:09,409 --> 00:05:10,611
HE CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

88
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:12,345
AS LONG AS HE'S
UNDER THOSE U. V. LIGHTS,

89
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:15,982
HE WILL REMAIN PETRIFIED
AND CAN POSE NO THREAT TO US.

90
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:18,585
( researcher #3 laughs )
THAT'S RIGHT.

91
00:05:18,652 --> 00:05:21,187
( researcher #2 laughs )
WELL, I SUPPOSE THAT'S A RELIEF.

92
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:23,824
Researcher #5: THERE IS STILL
MORE RESEARCH TO BE DONE

93
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:25,425
IF WE ARE
TO UNDERSTAND HIM FULLY.

94
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,459
♪

95
00:05:26,527 --> 00:05:27,460
( researchers gasp )

96
00:05:27,528 --> 00:05:28,595
Speedwagon: SEE THOSE?

97
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:30,531
THESE PICTURES
WERE TAKEN IN THE CAVE

98
00:05:30,597 --> 00:05:32,032
WHERE WE ORIGINALLY
FOUND SANTVIENTO.

99
00:05:32,132 --> 00:05:34,467
‐ INSPECT THEM CAREFULLY.
‐ ( researchers gasp )

100
00:05:34,535 --> 00:05:36,202
Researcher #5: THE HORNS.

101
00:05:36,302 --> 00:05:39,039
THEY ALL HAVE
DIFFERENT TYPES OF HORNS.

102
00:05:39,105 --> 00:05:40,874
Researcher #4:
SO IF THE ONE ON THE BOTTOM

103
00:05:40,974 --> 00:05:43,610
IS SUPPOSED TO BE SANTVIENTO,
THEN WHO ARE THE OTHERS?

104
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:45,211
Speedwagon:
ACCORDING TO VON STROHEIM,

105
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:47,380
THE GERMANS HAVE UNCOVERED
ANOTHER PILLAR

106
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,549
AT AN UNDISCLOSED LOCATION

107
00:05:48,649 --> 00:05:49,950
SOMEWHERE
ON THE EUROPEAN CONTINENT.

108
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:50,951
( researchers gasp )

109
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:52,218
Researcher #2: IS THAT TRUE?

110
00:05:52,318 --> 00:05:54,054
Speedwagon: THEIR FACES
ARE STACKED VERTICALLY

111
00:05:54,154 --> 00:05:55,722
IN THIS PICTURE.
SPEAKING HISTORICALLY,

112
00:05:55,822 --> 00:05:58,725
I WOULD THEORIZE THAT THIS
INDICATES STATUS OR RANK

113
00:05:58,825 --> 00:06:00,527
AMONG THE THREE PILLAR MEN.

114
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:02,368
JOJO AND I ARE HEADED TO ROME.

115
00:06:02,402 --> 00:06:04,705
VON STROHEIM TOLD HIM
THAT WE MUST GO THERE

116
00:06:04,738 --> 00:06:07,040
IN ORDER TO FIND
THE PERSON WHO CAN HELP US.

117
00:06:07,073 --> 00:06:10,911
AND IT TURNS OUT THAT PERSON...

118
00:06:11,011 --> 00:06:14,581
IS NONE OTHER THAN THE GRANDSON
OF WILL A. ZEPPELI,

119
00:06:14,681 --> 00:06:16,016
CAESAR ZEPPELI.

120
00:06:16,082 --> 00:06:18,752
Caesar: TELL ME,
WHERE MIGHT YOU BE FROM?

121
00:06:18,819 --> 00:06:20,654
WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO TAKE A PICTURE?

122
00:06:20,721 --> 00:06:22,388
PERHAPS ONE OF YOU
IN THE FOUNTAIN?

123
00:06:22,422 --> 00:06:23,389
Woman: HUH?

124
00:06:23,423 --> 00:06:24,558
( pigeons cooing )

125
00:06:24,591 --> 00:06:25,892
( JoJo imitates cooing )

126
00:06:25,926 --> 00:06:28,762
BOY, THE BIRDS IN THIS COUNTRY
SURE ARE FRIENDLY.

127
00:06:28,829 --> 00:06:31,197
THEY SEEM MUCH SMARTER
THAN THE MEN HERE, TOO.

128
00:06:31,264 --> 00:06:32,766
‐ DON'T YOU THINK?
‐ ( Caesar snorts )

129
00:06:32,866 --> 00:06:34,234
Speedwagon: KNOCK IT OFF, JOJO.

130
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:36,603
WE DIDN'T COME ALL THIS WAY
FOR NOTHING.

131
00:06:36,703 --> 00:06:38,171
THE TWO OF YOU
BETTER START TALKING.

132
00:06:38,238 --> 00:06:42,843
Caesar: MR. SPEEDWAGON,
I'M SORRY, BUT NOT A CHANCE.

133
00:06:42,909 --> 00:06:47,714
MY GRANDFATHER DIED TRAGICALLY
50 YEARS AGO.

134
00:06:47,781 --> 00:06:50,350
MY FATHER THEN TOOK UP HIS TORCH

135
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:53,119
AND SPENT HIS LIFE
HUNTING THE MASK.

136
00:06:53,219 --> 00:06:55,722
WE ITALIANS HAVE
THE STRONGEST FAMILIAL BONDS

137
00:06:55,789 --> 00:06:57,724
OF ANY CULTURE IN THE WORLD.

138
00:06:57,791 --> 00:06:59,893
WE ARE VERY PROUD
OF THAT TRADITION.

139
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:01,434
IT IS EVERYTHING TO US.

140
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:04,771
THAT'S SOMETHING
HE'LL NEVER UNDERSTAND.

141
00:07:04,805 --> 00:07:06,873
IN FACT, YOU TOLD ME
HE DIDN'T KNOW

142
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:08,709
ABOUT HIS OWN GRANDFATHER
UNTIL JUST RECENTLY.

143
00:07:08,775 --> 00:07:10,577
A TRUE MAN KNOWS HIS HISTORY.

144
00:07:10,644 --> 00:07:13,313
JoJo: TELL ME THIS, TRUE MAN.
IS YOUR WHOLE FAMILY THIS DUMB?

145
00:07:13,413 --> 00:07:14,548
Speedwagon:
THAT'S NOT FAIR, CAESAR.

146
00:07:14,615 --> 00:07:15,982
JOJO DIDN'T KNOW ANYTHING,

147
00:07:16,082 --> 00:07:17,918
BECAUSE I KEPT IT ALL
A SECRET FROM HIM.

148
00:07:17,984 --> 00:07:19,319
( Caesar sighs )

149
00:07:20,987 --> 00:07:22,956
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S ANY EXCUSE.

150
00:07:22,989 --> 00:07:24,224
I HEARD ABOUT STRAIZO,

151
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:26,159
AND I WAS IMPRESSED TO FIND OUT

152
00:07:26,226 --> 00:07:28,428
THAT HE FOUGHT
ONE OF THE PILLAR MEN.

153
00:07:28,494 --> 00:07:30,964
BUT I WANTED TO SEE FOR MYSELF
HOW TOUGH HE WAS,

154
00:07:30,997 --> 00:07:32,498
SO I WAITED AT THE HOTEL.

155
00:07:32,566 --> 00:07:34,234
AND I'M DISAPPOINTED TO SAY

156
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:37,237
THAT HIS HAMON SKILLS
LEAVE MUCH TO BE DESIRED.

157
00:07:37,303 --> 00:07:39,506
‐ HIS HAMON IS WEAK.
‐ ( JoJo sputtering )

158
00:07:39,606 --> 00:07:41,007
Caesar: IT'S WORTHLESS.

159
00:07:41,074 --> 00:07:45,011
HIS DEFEAT OF THE PILLAR MAN
WAS NOTHING BUT BLIND LUCK!

160
00:07:45,111 --> 00:07:48,348
I WON'T BE FORCED TO WORK
WITH THIS IMBECILE!

161
00:07:48,414 --> 00:07:50,817
Speedwagon: CAESAR,
JUST RELAX FOR A MOMENT.

162
00:07:50,851 --> 00:07:52,686
JOJO IS STILL TRAINING WITH‐‐

163
00:07:52,753 --> 00:07:53,920
( JoJo laughs )

164
00:07:53,987 --> 00:07:55,956
WE'RE DONE
WITH THE NICETIES HERE.

165
00:07:56,022 --> 00:07:57,457
( joints cracking )

166
00:07:57,524 --> 00:08:01,134
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO SETTLE THIS
WITH A GOOD THRASHING.

167
00:08:01,201 --> 00:08:03,136
Caesar: HAMON AS WEAK AS YOURS

168
00:08:03,203 --> 00:08:06,106
COULDN'T PLUCK THE PETALS
OFF THIS DELICATE FLOWER.

169
00:08:06,172 --> 00:08:08,008
( JoJo laughs ) OH, YEAH?

170
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:11,545
WELL, YOU COULDN'T EVEN
BEAT ONE OF THOSE PIGEONS.

171
00:08:11,612 --> 00:08:13,313
( Caesar chuckles )

172
00:08:14,615 --> 00:08:16,382
( JoJo gasps )

173
00:08:16,482 --> 00:08:19,485
( growls )
ARE YOU GONNA FIGHT ME OR NOT?

174
00:08:19,553 --> 00:08:21,487
IF THERE'S
ANY MOCKING TO BE DONE HERE,

175
00:08:21,555 --> 00:08:24,625
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT,
THANK YOU KINDLY.

176
00:08:24,691 --> 00:08:27,894
( gagging )

177
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:31,031
YOU...BASTARD.

178
00:08:31,064 --> 00:08:33,534
YOU GAVE THIS WOMAN
A HAMON KISS!

179
00:08:33,567 --> 00:08:35,368
Caesar: LIKE I JUST SAID,

180
00:08:35,401 --> 00:08:38,739
YOUR WEAK HAMON COULDN'T
EVEN DEFEAT A WOMAN. SAD.

181
00:08:38,805 --> 00:08:40,741
Speedwagon:
I MUST NOT INTERVENE HERE.

182
00:08:40,807 --> 00:08:43,243
THIS WILL BE
A GOOD LESSON FOR JOJO.

183
00:08:43,309 --> 00:08:46,079
OVERCOMING THIS
WILL ONLY MAKE HIM STRONGER.

184
00:08:48,481 --> 00:08:50,083
( JoJo screams )

185
00:08:51,017 --> 00:08:52,586
( Caesar scoffs )

186
00:08:52,686 --> 00:08:54,254
WHAT DID I TELL YOU?

187
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,923
MY GRANDFATHER
MIGHT STILL BE ALIVE

188
00:08:56,990 --> 00:08:59,425
IF YOUR GRANDFATHER
HADN'T GOT IN HIS WAY!

189
00:08:59,526 --> 00:09:03,269
I REFUSE TO ACCEPT YOUR KIND,
YOUR PATHETIC BLOOD.

190
00:09:03,336 --> 00:09:05,939
Speedwagon: THAT'S ENOUGH.
YOU'VE CROSSED THE LINE NOW.

191
00:09:06,039 --> 00:09:08,074
JoJo: STOP. I'VE GOT THIS.

192
00:09:08,108 --> 00:09:11,177
SOMEONE AS ARROGANT AS YOU
JUST COULDN'T RESIST

193
00:09:11,244 --> 00:09:13,379
INSULTING MY ENTIRE FAMILY,
COULD YOU?

194
00:09:14,781 --> 00:09:16,349
Caesar: LIKE TO SEE MY MANEUVER

195
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:18,118
SURE TO ELIMINATE
THE PILLAR MEN?

196
00:09:18,218 --> 00:09:19,452
IT'S A CLEAN TECHNIQUE.

197
00:09:20,721 --> 00:09:22,188
( flowing )

198
00:09:22,255 --> 00:09:24,691
BEHOLD!
MY HAMON BUBBLE LAUNCHER.

199
00:09:24,758 --> 00:09:26,059
( JoJo gasps )

200
00:09:26,126 --> 00:09:28,061
Caesar: IT'S IMPORTANT
TO KEEP ONESELF CLEAN.

201
00:09:28,128 --> 00:09:30,296
I, MYSELF,
HAVE A THIN LAYER OF SOAP

202
00:09:30,363 --> 00:09:31,798
ON MY CLOTHES AT ALL TIMES.

203
00:09:31,865 --> 00:09:36,770
YOU'RE LOOKING A LITTLE DIRTY
YOURSELF THERE, JOESTAR!

204
00:09:36,803 --> 00:09:38,471
JoJo: OHH!

205
00:09:39,806 --> 00:09:41,474
( screams )

206
00:09:41,575 --> 00:09:43,977
( grunting )

207
00:09:44,077 --> 00:09:47,113
( panting )

208
00:09:48,649 --> 00:09:50,083
Caesar: WELL, I AM IMPRESSED

209
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:51,585
THAT YOU'RE STILL CONSCIOUS,

210
00:09:51,652 --> 00:09:54,788
BUT YOUR WEAK LITTLE HAMON
COULDN'T EVEN POP A BUBBLE.

211
00:09:54,821 --> 00:09:58,925
JUST LOOK AT YOU. YOUR BREATH
IS ALREADY ALL OVER THE PLACE.

212
00:09:58,992 --> 00:10:00,794
ENJOY YOUR STAY, JOESTAR.

213
00:10:00,827 --> 00:10:04,538
JoJo: AND NEXT YOU'LL SAY,
"NOW I'LL LIFT MY HAMON SPELL,

214
00:10:04,605 --> 00:10:05,606
SIGNORINA. THANK YOU."

215
00:10:05,706 --> 00:10:08,909
Caesar: AND NOW
I'LL LIFT MY HAMON SPELL,

216
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,277
SIGNORINA. THANK YOU.

217
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:14,214
( gagging )

218
00:10:18,685 --> 00:10:20,554
( both panting )

219
00:10:20,621 --> 00:10:22,455
JoJo: WHILE THAT WOMAN
WAS THROTTLING ME,

220
00:10:22,556 --> 00:10:25,626
I FILLED THE PIGEON
WITH AS MUCH HAMON AS I COULD

221
00:10:25,726 --> 00:10:27,127
AND HID IT AWAY IN HER MOUTH.

222
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:29,129
‐ Caesar: MM?
‐ JoJo: I KNEW YOU'D KISS HER,

223
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:31,632
EITHER BECAUSE YOU HAD
TO WITHDRAW YOUR HAMON

224
00:10:31,698 --> 00:10:33,433
OR JUST TO SHOW OFF.

225
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:34,635
SO I WAS RIGHT.

226
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:37,538
TURNS OUT THAT YOU
COULDN'T EVEN BEAT A PIGEON.

227
00:10:37,604 --> 00:10:38,539
( Caesar scoffs )

228
00:10:38,605 --> 00:10:40,907
( JoJo laughs )

229
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:43,544
( Speedwagon sighs )
WHAT A DAY.

230
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:45,478
♪

231
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:55,822
JoJo: HONESTLY, JUST WHO
DOES THIS JERK THINK HE IS?

232
00:10:55,889 --> 00:10:59,292
GRANDSTANDING LIKE THAT
JUST TO SIT DOWN IN A CHAIR.

233
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,568
I REALLY CAN'T STAND
PEOPLE LIKE HIM.

234
00:11:01,635 --> 00:11:05,471
IF ONLY I HAD A TECHNIQUE
LIKE HIS BUBBLE LAUNCHER.

235
00:11:05,506 --> 00:11:08,408
I'D BE ABLE TO TEACH HIM
SOME HUMILITY THEN.

236
00:11:08,474 --> 00:11:12,178
I HAVE TO GET STRONGER
WITH MY HAMON,

237
00:11:12,245 --> 00:11:15,081
BUT TRAINING
IS ALWAYS SUCH A HASSLE.

238
00:11:15,148 --> 00:11:17,584
HMM. LET'S SEE
HOW OUR LITTLE FRIEND

239
00:11:17,651 --> 00:11:19,786
HANDLES A GAME OF CHANCE.

240
00:11:19,853 --> 00:11:21,321
Caesar: I SAW THAT, JOJO.

241
00:11:21,354 --> 00:11:23,657
DEAL THE CARDS RIGHT.
ONLY COWARDS CHEAT.

242
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:25,826
JoJo: HUH? WHATEVER DO YOU‐‐

243
00:11:25,859 --> 00:11:30,030
Caesar: DEAL THE CARDS PROPERLY,
JOESTAR, OR PLAY ELSEWHERE.

244
00:11:30,096 --> 00:11:32,365
( JoJo stammers )
FANCY THAT.

245
00:11:32,465 --> 00:11:35,201
WELL, THAT DIDN'T WORK.
( chuckles )

246
00:11:35,268 --> 00:11:36,770
( Caesar scoffs )
PATHETIC.

247
00:11:36,837 --> 00:11:39,540
YOU SHOULD BE ASHAMED
THAT YOU HAVE TO RESORT

248
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,675
TO CHEATING AND GIMMICKS
TO BEAT ME.

249
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:44,277
JoJo: YOU REALLY ARE SERIOUS
ABOUT CLEANLINESS.

250
00:11:44,344 --> 00:11:45,846
THIS MIRROR IS SPOTLESS.

251
00:11:45,879 --> 00:11:47,280
Caesar:
STOP PROVOKING ME, JOESTAR!

252
00:11:47,347 --> 00:11:49,015
JoJo: OH,
I HAVEN'T EVEN STARTED!

253
00:11:49,049 --> 00:11:50,383
Speedwagon: CALM DOWN!

254
00:11:50,483 --> 00:11:52,152
IT'S BEEN EIGHT HOURS, CAESAR.

255
00:11:52,218 --> 00:11:55,055
DO YOU MIND TELLING US
WHAT WE'RE WAITING FOR?

256
00:11:55,121 --> 00:11:56,056
( Caesar sighs )

257
00:11:56,122 --> 00:11:57,057
( clock ticking )

258
00:11:57,123 --> 00:11:59,225
JoJo: WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

259
00:12:00,393 --> 00:12:02,736
Caesar: HERE'S YOUR ANSWER.

260
00:12:05,572 --> 00:12:09,342
( JoJo gasps ) WHAT THE HELL
IS A GERMAN SOLDIER DOING HERE?

261
00:12:10,376 --> 00:12:12,178
Caesar: IT LOOKS
LIKE WE'RE CLEAR.

262
00:12:12,245 --> 00:12:13,580
( Speedwagon and JoJo gasp )

263
00:12:13,647 --> 00:12:16,249
Caesar: JUST WHO DO YOU THINK
GUARDS THE PILLAR MEN?

264
00:12:16,349 --> 00:12:18,184
HE'LL GET US IN THERE.
BEHAVE YOURSELF.

265
00:12:18,251 --> 00:12:20,987
JoJo: AGAIN WITH THE GERMANS?

266
00:12:21,054 --> 00:12:23,189
♪

267
00:12:40,273 --> 00:12:42,843
Caesar: GERMANY AND ITALY
HAVE AN ALLIANCE,

268
00:12:42,909 --> 00:12:44,545
AND THE GERMANS ARE INTERESTED

269
00:12:44,611 --> 00:12:47,280
IN RESEARCHING
THE NUANCES OF MY HAMON, SEE?

270
00:12:47,347 --> 00:12:49,015
YOU ENGLISHMEN ARE VERY LUCKY

271
00:12:49,082 --> 00:12:52,619
THAT YOU ARE BEING GRANTED
ACCESS TO VIEW THE PILLAR MEN.

272
00:12:52,686 --> 00:12:54,555
NO NEED TO THANK ME.

273
00:12:54,621 --> 00:12:57,624
YOUR APPRECIATION'S
WRITTEN ON YOUR FACE, JOJO.

274
00:12:57,691 --> 00:12:59,392
‐ Soldier: MR. SPEEDWAGON...
‐ Speedwagon: HUH?

275
00:12:59,459 --> 00:13:01,434
Soldier: WE HAVE
SO MANY QUESTIONS FOR YOU.

276
00:13:01,467 --> 00:13:03,436
I HOPE THAT WE
CAN ALL WORK TOGETHER

277
00:13:03,469 --> 00:13:05,238
TO STOP THE PILLAR MEN
BEFORE THEY AWAKE.

278
00:13:05,305 --> 00:13:06,239
( JoJo scoffs )

279
00:13:06,306 --> 00:13:08,241
Caesar: HOW IS THE BEAUTY?

280
00:13:08,308 --> 00:13:09,309
Soldier: HUH?

281
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:10,577
Caesar: NOW DON'T BE EMBARRASSED

282
00:13:10,644 --> 00:13:12,245
YOU HAVE A GIRLFRIEND BACK HOME.

283
00:13:12,312 --> 00:13:13,747
Soldier: WELL. SHE'S‐‐

284
00:13:13,814 --> 00:13:17,150
UH, ACTUALLY, THE TRUTH IS
I'LL BE GOING HOME NEXT WEEK

285
00:13:17,217 --> 00:13:18,985
SO WE CAN FINALLY GET MARRIED.

286
00:13:19,052 --> 00:13:20,053
Caesar: REALLY?

287
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:22,422
MAMMA MIA!
CONGRATULATIONS, MARK.

288
00:13:22,488 --> 00:13:26,059
I WAS HIS WINGMAN
WHEN HE PICKED HER UP, YOU KNOW.

289
00:13:26,126 --> 00:13:27,761
‐ HE WAS SO NERVOUS.
‐ JoJo: HEARTWARMING.

290
00:13:27,828 --> 00:13:29,830
PLEASE DON'T
GET US ALL KILLED HERE.

291
00:13:29,930 --> 00:13:33,934
AND PLEASE STOP CUDDLING WITH
THE WHEEL, IF YOU DON'T MIND.

292
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,169
Caesar: I WANTED
TO ASK YOU, JOJO,

293
00:13:36,269 --> 00:13:38,639
DO YOU HAVE
A GIRLFRIEND BACK HOME?

294
00:13:38,672 --> 00:13:39,506
( JoJo grumbles )

295
00:13:39,573 --> 00:13:41,241
Caesar: I'LL TAKE THAT AS A NO.

296
00:13:41,307 --> 00:13:42,743
BUT YOU'RE SUCH A GREAT CATCH.

297
00:13:42,809 --> 00:13:44,678
WHY DOESN'T ANYONE
WANT TO DATE YOU?

298
00:13:44,745 --> 00:13:48,081
PERHAPS THEY'RE ALL TOO BUSY
WASHING THEIR HAIR, EH?

299
00:13:48,148 --> 00:13:49,182
( laughing )

300
00:13:49,282 --> 00:13:50,951
JoJo: WHERE DOES
THIS POMPOUS ASS

301
00:13:51,017 --> 00:13:52,519
GET OFF TALKING TO ME LIKE THAT?

302
00:13:52,619 --> 00:13:54,855
ONCE I DEVELOP
MY OWN KILLER TECHNIQUE,

303
00:13:54,921 --> 00:13:56,857
I'LL SHOW HIM A THING OR TWO

304
00:13:56,957 --> 00:13:57,858
OR THREE.

305
00:13:59,926 --> 00:14:02,803
♪

306
00:14:02,869 --> 00:14:04,871
Soldier: LOOK!
THERE'S SOMETHING ON HIS HEAD.

307
00:14:04,971 --> 00:14:07,608
Soldier #2: I DON'T THINK
THAT WAS THERE BEFORE.

308
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:10,677
Officer: CALM DOWN.
THEY'RE JUST ROCKS

309
00:14:10,711 --> 00:14:13,213
AS LONG AS THEY'RE
UNDER THOSE U. V. LIGHTS.

310
00:14:13,279 --> 00:14:14,447
NO NEED TO WORRY.

311
00:14:14,515 --> 00:14:16,049
NOW GET A CLOSER LOOK!

312
00:14:16,149 --> 00:14:17,350
Soldier #3: YES, SIR.

313
00:14:17,383 --> 00:14:19,385
Officer: THE DEATH
OF VON STROHEIM'S TEAM

314
00:14:19,485 --> 00:14:21,555
IS AN IMPORTANT LESSON
TO US ALL.

315
00:14:21,655 --> 00:14:24,825
ONCE WE CUT THIS PILLAR OUT,
WE'LL HAVE TO SEAL IT

316
00:14:24,891 --> 00:14:28,028
SO THAT IT WILL NEVER SEE
THE LIGHT OF DAY AGAIN.

317
00:14:28,061 --> 00:14:30,631
Soldier #3: I CAN'T TELL
WHAT THAT DARK SPOT IS.

318
00:14:30,697 --> 00:14:33,900
IT LOOKS LIKE A HOLE,
BUT IT MIGHT JUST BE A SHADOW.

319
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,368
Soldier #2: GET A CLOSER LOOK.

320
00:14:35,401 --> 00:14:36,369
Soldier #3: EH?

321
00:14:36,402 --> 00:14:37,904
( wind blows )

322
00:14:39,506 --> 00:14:41,908
D‐DO YOU HEAR THAT?

323
00:14:42,008 --> 00:14:43,510
( gags )

324
00:14:43,577 --> 00:14:44,878
‐ ( soldiers gasp )
‐ Soldier #2: HIS HORN!

325
00:14:44,911 --> 00:14:47,080
Officer: HE'S SUPPOSED
TO BE PETRIFIED!

326
00:14:47,180 --> 00:14:51,017
‐ ( crackling )
‐ HE'S WAKING UP!

327
00:14:51,084 --> 00:14:53,720
QUICKLY!
BRING OUT MORE U. V. LAMPS!

328
00:14:53,754 --> 00:14:55,656
‐ Soldier #4: YES, SIR!
‐ Officer: SCHNELL!

329
00:14:58,158 --> 00:15:00,266
( soldiers gag )

330
00:15:01,768 --> 00:15:02,736
( all gasping )

331
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:04,705
Officer: THIS CAN'T
BE HAPPENING!

332
00:15:04,771 --> 00:15:09,109
HE'S BLOCKING OUT THE LIGHTS
WITH THE BLOOD OF MY OWN MEN!

333
00:15:09,175 --> 00:15:11,578
♪

334
00:15:22,523 --> 00:15:25,125
( joints crack )

335
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:26,893
Pillar Man: I SEE THE WORLD

336
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:30,130
HAS UNDERGONE SIGNIFICANT
CHANGES DURING MY SLUMBER.

337
00:15:30,196 --> 00:15:33,600
THESE INSIGNIFICANT INVENTIONS
MUST BE QUITE POPULAR HERE.

338
00:15:33,634 --> 00:15:34,868
Officer: WHAT'D HE SAY?!

339
00:15:34,935 --> 00:15:37,370
Pillar Man: I SAID
YOUR PITIFUL ILLUMINATIONS

340
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:39,573
ARE NO MATCH AGAINST MY POWER.

341
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,444
( soldiers scream )

342
00:15:44,477 --> 00:15:45,646
Soldier #4: MY HANDS!

343
00:15:46,613 --> 00:15:48,314
Soldiers: WE'RE STUCK TOGETHER!

344
00:15:48,381 --> 00:15:50,651
( officer gasps )

345
00:15:50,717 --> 00:15:51,652
( yells )

346
00:15:52,819 --> 00:15:54,955
( gasping )

347
00:15:57,457 --> 00:15:59,593
( soldiers groaning )

348
00:16:08,942 --> 00:16:09,843
WAMUU!

349
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:13,814
NOW IS THE TIME.

350
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:15,816
AWAKEN, MY MASTERS!

351
00:16:15,849 --> 00:16:17,584
♪

352
00:16:24,490 --> 00:16:26,627
( footsteps echoing )

353
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,130
( JoJo gasps )

354
00:16:30,196 --> 00:16:31,632
Speedwagon: SOMEHOW,
THIS DOESN'T SURPRISE ME.

355
00:16:31,698 --> 00:16:32,766
THE FAMOUS MOUTH OF TRUTH

356
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:35,669
WAS A SECRET ENTRANCE
ALL THIS TIME.

357
00:16:38,204 --> 00:16:40,941
♪

358
00:16:41,007 --> 00:16:44,044
YOU CAN REALLY FEEL
THE CHILL OF THE DEAD HERE.

359
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:45,378
CAESAR, WHAT SORT OF EFFECTS

360
00:16:45,445 --> 00:16:47,714
HAS YOUR HAMON HAD
ON THE SLEEPING PILLAR MEN?

361
00:16:47,814 --> 00:16:50,383
Caesar: HAMON IS ONLY USEFUL
ON THE LIVING.

362
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:52,786
NO REASON TO WASTE
MY POWERS ON STONE.

363
00:16:52,853 --> 00:16:54,888
WE CAN'T LEARN ANYTHING
IF THEY'RE NOT ALIVE.

364
00:16:54,955 --> 00:16:56,056
Speedwagon: HMM.

365
00:16:56,122 --> 00:16:58,559
JoJo: I'M SURPRISED
YOU GERMANS DON'T HAVE

366
00:16:58,659 --> 00:17:01,301
MORE THAN, UH,
ZERO GUARDS DOWN HERE.

367
00:17:01,367 --> 00:17:03,670
IT'S A LITTLE QUIET. HELLO?!

368
00:17:03,737 --> 00:17:05,639
Caesar:
STOP BEING FOOLISH, JOJO.

369
00:17:05,706 --> 00:17:06,873
Mark: WAIT. SOMETHING'S WRONG.

370
00:17:06,907 --> 00:17:08,474
‐ Caesar: HMM?
‐ Mark: HE'S RIGHT.

371
00:17:08,542 --> 00:17:10,544
THERE SHOULD BE GUARDS POSTED
ALL AROUND THIS PLACE.

372
00:17:10,577 --> 00:17:11,978
Caesar: HUH? REALLY?

373
00:17:12,045 --> 00:17:12,979
( JoJo scoffs )

374
00:17:13,046 --> 00:17:13,980
( escaping gas toots )

375
00:17:14,047 --> 00:17:15,215
YAAH!

376
00:17:15,248 --> 00:17:18,084
WHY DIDN'T ANYONE TELL ME
THERE WERE BATS IN HERE?

377
00:17:18,151 --> 00:17:19,586
GROSS. I STEPPED IN BAT DUNG!

378
00:17:19,653 --> 00:17:22,856
AND I JUST CLEANED THESE.

379
00:17:24,090 --> 00:17:25,759
( Mark gasps )

380
00:17:27,594 --> 00:17:29,495
JoJo: WAIT. THOSE ARE...

381
00:17:29,563 --> 00:17:31,497
Caesar: THEY'RE HUSKS
OF DEAD SOLDIERS.

382
00:17:31,565 --> 00:17:34,434
Mark: WHAT‐‐WHAT THE HELL
HAPPENED TO THEM?

383
00:17:34,535 --> 00:17:36,770
THEY'RE ALL DEAD! ( screams )

384
00:17:36,837 --> 00:17:37,938
JoJo: STOP WHERE YOU ARE!

385
00:17:38,004 --> 00:17:39,706
WHOEVER DID THIS
COULD STILL BE HERE!

386
00:17:39,773 --> 00:17:42,342
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT'S OUT THERE!

387
00:17:42,408 --> 00:17:43,710
( Mark screams )

388
00:17:43,777 --> 00:17:45,411
JoJo: WHAT‐‐WHAT IS THAT?

389
00:17:45,445 --> 00:17:47,548
Speedwagon: I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
THEY'RE‐‐THEY'RE ALIVE!

390
00:17:47,614 --> 00:17:48,615
Caesar: RUN AWAY, MARK!

391
00:17:48,682 --> 00:17:50,951
GET OUT OF THERE NOW!

392
00:17:51,051 --> 00:17:53,787
NO!

393
00:17:54,921 --> 00:17:57,758
( Mark gasps )

394
00:18:00,026 --> 00:18:01,467
( all gasp )

395
00:18:01,535 --> 00:18:04,470
Caesar: MARK!

396
00:18:04,538 --> 00:18:07,107
( Mark gasping )

397
00:18:08,975 --> 00:18:09,943
Caesar: MARK, NO.

398
00:18:11,111 --> 00:18:12,779
Mark: CAESAR. CAESAR.

399
00:18:12,813 --> 00:18:14,981
Caesar: WHAT HAVE THEY DONE?!

400
00:18:15,048 --> 00:18:17,250
Speedwagon: THEY JUST WALKED
RIGHT THROUGH YOUR FRIEND

401
00:18:17,317 --> 00:18:18,619
LIKE HE WASN'T EVEN THERE.

402
00:18:18,652 --> 00:18:20,921
THE PILLAR MEN HAVE AWOKEN
WITH SUCH MASSIVE POWER

403
00:18:20,987 --> 00:18:22,789
THAT WE BARELY
EVEN EXIST TO THEM.

404
00:18:22,823 --> 00:18:24,991
WE MAY AS WELL BE NOTHING MORE

405
00:18:25,091 --> 00:18:27,928
THAN A COLONY OF ANTS
BENEATH THEIR FEET.

406
00:18:30,664 --> 00:18:34,500
Pillar Man #2: IT APPEARS
TO BE NIGHT OUTSIDE, WAMUU.

407
00:18:34,568 --> 00:18:36,302
Wamuu: THAT IS CORRECT,
LORD KARS.

408
00:18:36,336 --> 00:18:37,938
AND WHAT SHALL BE YOUR BIDDING?

409
00:18:38,004 --> 00:18:40,440
Pillar Man #3: EASY.
WE WILL BE SEARCHING

410
00:18:40,507 --> 00:18:43,276
FOR THE WHEREABOUTS
OF THE RED STONE OF AJA.

411
00:18:43,343 --> 00:18:45,812
THE STONE IS
THE LAST PIECE WE NEED

412
00:18:45,846 --> 00:18:47,814
IN ORDER TO COMPLETE THE MASK.

413
00:18:47,848 --> 00:18:50,016
THEN WE WILL UNLEASH
ITS POWER.

414
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:51,785
Wamuu: OF COURSE,
MASTER ESIDISI.

415
00:18:51,852 --> 00:18:54,254
HOWEVER, THE HUMAN WORLD
HAS CHANGED MUCH

416
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:55,989
OVER THE YEARS
THAT WE SLUMBERED.

417
00:18:56,022 --> 00:19:00,594
LONG AGO, IT WAS THE EMPEROR
OF ROME WHO POSSESSED THE STONE.

418
00:19:00,661 --> 00:19:03,937
UNFORTUNATELY, I AM CERTAIN
THAT AGE HAS ENDED.

419
00:19:04,004 --> 00:19:06,673
Kars: WELL, THEN,
WE SIMPLY NEED TO FIND

420
00:19:06,707 --> 00:19:09,342
WHERE IT IS THE STONE
CURRENTLY CALLS HOME.

421
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:10,844
Wamuu: THEY SAY THE EMPEROR

422
00:19:10,877 --> 00:19:12,813
CHERISHED THE STONE
ABOVE ALL THINGS.

423
00:19:12,879 --> 00:19:16,717
I BELIEVE THAT THE HUMANS OF
TODAY STILL TELL STORIES OF IT.

424
00:19:16,783 --> 00:19:19,720
I SHALL RETRIEVE THE STONE
FOR YOU, MY MASTER.

425
00:19:19,786 --> 00:19:21,187
Kars: THERE'S TIME, WAMUU.

426
00:19:21,221 --> 00:19:22,723
Esidisi: FOR THE MOMENT THEN,

427
00:19:22,789 --> 00:19:25,458
LET US GO OUTSIDE
AND OBSERVE THE CHANGES

428
00:19:25,526 --> 00:19:27,894
THAT HAVE OCCURRED
IN THE HUMAN WORLD.

429
00:19:27,994 --> 00:19:28,895
Kars: HMM.

430
00:19:34,234 --> 00:19:35,235
( Wamuu grunts )

431
00:19:40,741 --> 00:19:42,408
‐ ( gasps )
‐ Esidisi: WAMUU!

432
00:19:42,475 --> 00:19:44,244
EXPLAIN YOUR INSOLENCE.

433
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:45,979
Kars: STAY YOUR HAND, ESIDISI.

434
00:19:47,681 --> 00:19:49,916
Wamuu: I APOLOGIZE, LORD KARS.

435
00:19:49,983 --> 00:19:53,086
Kars: OF COURSE.
IT HAD SLIPPED MY MIND

436
00:19:53,186 --> 00:19:55,088
THAT YOU POSSESS
A REFLEXIVE ATTACK

437
00:19:55,155 --> 00:19:57,057
AGAINST ANYONE
WHO DARES TO WALK

438
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:59,359
ACROSS THE DEPTHS
OF YOUR SHADOW.

439
00:19:59,425 --> 00:20:01,602
IT HAS BEEN 2,000 YEARS,
AFTER ALL.

440
00:20:01,668 --> 00:20:03,670
Wamuu: I HAVE OFFENDED YOU,
MY LORD.

441
00:20:03,704 --> 00:20:06,306
I WILL ACCEPT
WHATEVER PUNISHMENT YOU SEE FIT.

442
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:07,440
( Kars chuckles )

443
00:20:07,508 --> 00:20:09,876
I SIMPLY CANNOT ACCEPT
YOUR APOLOGY.

444
00:20:09,976 --> 00:20:12,646
YOUR INNATE FIGHTING SPIRIT
IS WHAT MAKES YOU

445
00:20:12,713 --> 00:20:15,782
A GREAT WARRIOR,
AND THAT IS WHY I TRUST YOU.

446
00:20:15,849 --> 00:20:19,219
THE FAULT IS MY OWN
FOR TREADING UPON YOUR DARKNESS.

447
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:20,787
PLEASE FORGIVE MY TRANSGRESSION.

448
00:20:20,854 --> 00:20:22,523
Wamuu: YOU ARE TOO KIND.

449
00:20:22,556 --> 00:20:24,525
( Kars chuckles )

450
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:27,027
RISE, WAMUU.

451
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:28,529
Wamuu: YES, MASTER.

452
00:20:28,562 --> 00:20:32,132
( Mark groaning ) CAESAR!

453
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:33,534
KILL ME, PLEASE. DO IT.

454
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:35,168
YOU'VE GOT TO KILL ME NOW.

455
00:20:35,235 --> 00:20:36,236
Caesar: I CAN'T.

456
00:20:36,302 --> 00:20:39,540
Mark: IT'S‐‐
IT'S GETTING SO COLD.

457
00:20:39,573 --> 00:20:40,641
PLEASE, CAESAR.

458
00:20:40,707 --> 00:20:43,209
I'M‐‐I'M SO SCARED.

459
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:45,746
I COULDN'T FEEL ANYTHING
AT FIRST,

460
00:20:45,812 --> 00:20:47,247
BUT NOW, THE PAIN.

461
00:20:47,347 --> 00:20:50,216
PLEASE, CAESAR,
